Rating: 4
This is a great recipe "as-is," no modifications required (or desired!). Fast, easy, delicious. It certainly qualifies as a dish for dinner guests, and is a very tasty way to deal with holiday turkey leftovers. You really must use fresh tarragon, or else the results won't be as spectacular. I use Noilly Prat in just about every recipe that calls for white wine and find that it works brilliantly well with this one. Can't help but comment on a few other reviews: Don't confuse subtlety in flavours with "blandness." If it's overpowering, you've done it wrong. The dish is delightfully flavourful, especially if you use fresh tarragon (and the Noilly Prat adds a certain something, too...). Also, the sauce isn't supposed to be some heavy, thick, glutinous concoction. If you use the right cream and pay attention to what you're doing, the sauce will thicken to just the right consistency on its own (just so it coats the spoon) without ruining it with thickeners.

