Rating: 4
I have made this dish a number of times and my family absolutely loves it. I understand the problem some reviewers have had with the sauce seeming too thin. This is how I solve that problem: I sauté only the mushrooms in the butter until the liquid they expel is almost reabsorbed, then I continue with the recipe as written. I found that this eliminates a lot of liquid which thinned the sauce - this revised method allows the sauce to thicken up beautifully. Personally I use a just bit less wine and in its place add a handful of fresh, seeded/diced tomatoes to add color and flavor. I use about a tablespoon (+/-) of dried tarragon because we like the flavor better than fresh, and generously season with salt and pepper throughout. Delicious!

